description: From Middle English withcallen, equivalent to with- (“back, away”) +‎ call.

verbs.description: withcall (third-person singular simple present withcalls, present participle withcalling, simple past and past participle withcalled)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To call back or call away (from); recall; withdraw one's words; retract; recant; unsay; cancel; call off.
examples: [...] intended to withcall him from his Studies, [...]
